out the play and playwright. This range of material, rare in a single volume, provides several reading and teaching options, from the study of a single author to an overview of the entire Classical comedic tradition. The plays have been translated for readability and fidelity to the original text by established Classics scholars. Douglas Olson provides the translation and commentary for Aristophanes' Acharnians, Shawn O'Bryhim for Menander's Dyskolos, George Fredric Franco for Plautus' Casina, and Timothy J. Moore for Terence's Phormio.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aClassical drama (Comedy)vTranslations into English. 0aClassical drama (Comedy)xHistory and criticism. 7aDRAMA / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh1 aFranko, George Fredric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFranko, George Fredric.1 aMoore, Timothy J.1 aMoore, Timothy J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO'Bryhim, Shawn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aO'Bryhim, Shawn.1 aOlson, S. Douglas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlson, S. Douglas.1 aO’Bryhim, Shawn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/76054740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292797901423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292797901/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK